@ewencp @hachikuji I'd appreciate your reviews. 

Couple of things. Intervention in tests is minimal since the current coverage seems sufficient and the implementation refers mostly to code residing in private scope. But I'll give it a second look. 

Parallelization was applied in DistributedHerder only. If the approach seems plausible we could consider application on Standalone as well. Although as mentioned in the original jira ticket, this isn't crusial.

@guozhangwang Just realized, that I forget to commit something which fails left-join tests...

About inner-join: that is exactly the timing issues we discussed already. The integration test is super slow... not sure why it takes to long for the result consumer to receive output records...
If you observe system-out you will see that it take multiple seconds -- and sometime even longer...
